parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various issues, including ignition problems, camera malfunctions, and loss of motive power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Intermittent failure of the back over protection camera
ignition key being loose and requiring forceful pressing and turning to start the vehicle
vehicle not immediately starting while pressing the ignition switch
and loss of motive power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause sudden and unexpected braking, loss of brakes, or failure of the automatic braking system, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: failure of the automatic braking system

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the air conditioner to malfunction, leading to hot air blowing out of the vents, and potentially causing engine overheating.
symptoms: Hot air blowing out of the air conditioner vents

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the chassis control system can cause various issues, including error messages, flashing instrument diagrams, and buzzing sounds, which can lead to driver distraction and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Error messages on the instrument panel
and failure of various systems such as the radio and clock.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the backup camera can increase the risk of accidents or injuries while reversing, as the driver may not be able to see obstacles or pedestrians behind the vehicle.
symptoms: The backup camera displays a blurry or grayed-out image
making it difficult or impossible to see obstacles or pedestrians behind the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator pulley can cause the vehicle to overheat and break down, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: causing the belt to melt onto the pulley
and the vehicle overheats and breaks down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning system can cause the vehicle to overheat, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The air conditioning system stops blowing cold air
mist or fog comes out of the AC vents
and the vehicle does not cool even when the AC is set to maximum.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the automatic emergency braking system can cause the vehicle to stop suddenly, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries, especially if other vehicles are following closely behind.
symptoms: The automatic emergency braking system engages randomly
causing the vehicle to stop suddenly
even when there are no obstacles or hazards present.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of the automatic braking system can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop or swerve, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly brakes or stops without warning
the automatic emergency braking system activates without any obstruction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause loss of motive power, sudden acceleration, and jerking movements, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
Failure of the shift lock solenoid can cause the vehicle to accelerate on its own, fail to shift gears, and make it difficult to control the vehicle, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: clutch pedal feels soft or spongy

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Back Over Prevention Camera Screen Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the back over prevention camera screen can reduce visibility and increase the risk of accidents or injuries when reversing.
symptoms: Back over prevention camera screen goes blank
and instrument cluster lights fail to operate as needed.
